725558f-a.text:
65th Street, west side, at 62nd Ave. (center of view), showing in the foreground at the S.W. corner, the former Mount Olivet Hotel. This hotel which was owned in 1891 by Wels and Eerweck was operated by Louis
Niederstein Jr. Beyond it is the Fresh Pond Crematory.
January 1924.
Eumene L. Armbruster Collection.
